commit.message: For issue#92, flip the sense of the "USE_INSTALLED_TRE_H" flag and rename it to "USE_LOCAL_TRE_H", then add definitions in all local builds.
Wrap up the last bit of PR#19 together with change for new "local_includes" directory.
Update README.md with a pointer to the updated REAME_waf.txt file.

Update autotools input files for the rename of "include/tre" to "local_includes".
(Missed in previous commit.)

Move the "#include" headers for libtre from "include/tre" to "local_includes" as a way to ensure the local header is used.
Before this change it was possible for a build of the python extension
or agrep to pick up the "tre.h" header file from an installed TRE
package that had been configured differently from the current build.

Hand merge of the last parts of PR#49 from ahomansikka (possibly also Hannu Väisänen <Hannu.Vaisanen@uef.fi>)
I'm not clear on who is who with this, my apologies if I've given credit
incorrectly.
Hand merge of PR#83 by bucanero to new "contrib" directory for PS3 port.
Small change to README.md to give the full path to the tre.h header file and describe is as a source of additional hints.

commit.message:
Hand merge of PR#80 from DL6ER to add distinct error message for maximum number in {} being too large.
This uses a different approach for the encoding of the tests/retest.c
source code, but includes the additional test of the new error message
in tests/retest.c.

Add the []'s around "utils" for "AC_CONFIG_AUX_DIR([utils])" in file config.ac.
This configures, builds, and passes "make check" on both Linux and FreeBSD,
and is consistent with the other AC_... macro calls in the file.
This was suggested by Elizabeth Myers to fix a build of tre for Adélie
Linux that uses gettext-tiny where the build process failed because of the
missing []'s.
Update README_waf.txt.

Rework the waf build system's creation of the python virtual environment
used for testing the python extension so that it happens at build time
and not at configuration time.
Improve the behaviour or the "waf install" command slightly.

Fix: Change indentation to eliminate a gcc warning [-Wmisleading-indentation]
     No change to semantics, and now matches indentation of similar
     transition cost setting code earlier in file.
Fix: waf build changes required for PR#84.
